name: Nevergreen
description:
Nevergreen is a build monitor with attitude. It has two distinct features that set it apart:

1) Your builds should always be green. Nevergreen understands this and only shows you jobs that have failed or are building.
2) Nevergreen uses HTML localStorage. So the config is stored in your web browser. You only need to run it once to host hundreds of different build monitors.

name: A yeoman generator for Java projects.
description:
java-bones is a yeoman-generator for Java-projects using maven. java-bones creates a project that uses
-    a GPL3 license,
-   static code analysis and reports using pmd and checkstyle ,
-    a unit-test suite using JUnit and logging using log4j/slf4j,
-    badges for the project status, build status using Travis CI and code coverage using Jacoco,
-    custom README.md, TODO.md and VERSIONS.md files and
-   a prototype Main.java + TestSuite.java.

name: Kitodo.Production
description: Kitodo.Production is an open source software intended to support and manage workflows in digitization projects for cultural heritage institutions. Kitodo consists of several independent modules serving different purposes, such as presenting the digitized media to the public in a modern and convenient way, e.g. prints, newspapers and magazines, manuscripts and letters, sheet music, broadsheets, archivalia, and digital depositary copies.
